a.title: ― Universe: Specialized unit type, with the specialization based upon characteristics other than time and geography.
a.xlink:title: ― Universe: Specialized unit type, with the specialization based upon characteristics other than time and geography.

a.title: ― DimensionalKeyDefinitionMember: Single concept that is part of a dimensional key definition.
a.xlink:title: ― DimensionalKeyDefinitionMember: Single concept that is part of a dimensional key definition.

a.title: ― DimensionalKey: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a dimensional dataset.
a.xlink:title: ― DimensionalKey: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a dimensional dataset.

a.title: ― ScopedMeasure: A qualified measure whose domain is a universe as an aggregate, i.e. a measure with a specific production method applied to a specific cell in a cube.
a.xlink:title: ― ScopedMeasure: A qualified measure whose domain is a universe as an aggregate, i.e. a measure with a specific production method applied to a specific cell in a cube.

a.title: ― KeyDefinition: Collection of concepts that uniquely defines a collection of data points in a dataset.
a.xlink:title: ― KeyDefinition: Collection of concepts that uniquely defines a collection of data points in a dataset.

a.title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.
a.xlink:title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.

a.title: ― providesSemanticTo: Dimensional key definition provides semantic to zero to one universe.
a.xlink:title: ― providesSemanticTo: Dimensional key definition provides semantic to zero to one universe.

a.title: ― circumscribes: A universe is specific to the specific cell associated with a scoped measure.
a.xlink:title: ― circumscribes: A universe is specific to the specific cell associated with a scoped measure.
